Scientific and methodological attribution
================================================================================

## Daniels-Gilbert equations

The deterministic pace-zone and training-intensity layer of this project is
derived from the oxygen-cost and race-prediction equations originally
published by Jack Daniels and Jimmy Gilbert in:

    Daniels, J. and Gilbert, J. (1979). Oxygen Power: Performance Tables for
    Distance Runners. Tempe, AZ: Oxygen Power.

Only the mathematical formulations are used; no tabular or textual content
from the monograph is reproduced in this repository. See the decision log
(docs/decisions/decision-log.md) for the derivation methodology.

"VDOT" is a trademark of The Run SMART Project LLC. This project is not
affiliated with, endorsed by, or licensed by The Run SMART Project LLC.
User-facing surface in this project refers to these values as
"Daniels-Gilbert zones" or generic pace-zone terminology.

## Tanaka heart-rate formula

The estimated maximum heart rate calculation uses the age-predicted formula
published in:

    Tanaka, H., Monahan, K. D., and Seals, D. R. (2001). Age-predicted
    maximal heart rate revisited. Journal of the American College of
    Cardiology, 37(1), 153-156.

